https://leetcode.com/problems/number-of-provinces/description/

QUESTION:
Input: isConnected = [[1,1,0],[1,1,0],[0,0,1]]
Output: 2

Input: isConnected = [[1,0,0],[0,1,0],[0,0,1]]
Output: 3

SOLUTION:
  0 1 2
0 1 1 0
1 1 1 0
2 0 0 1
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
TIME COMPLEXITY:O(n*n)
SPACE COMPLEXITY: O(n*n)

each row is a city
city i==j is a self loop.
city 0 -> city 1 =1 so it is connceted
city 0 -> city 2 =0 it is not connected
city 1 -> city 0 =1 it is connected 
...
create a map where you store the values
visited hashset and dfs through the path.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CODE:
class Solution {
    public int findCircleNum(int[][] isConnected) {
        HashMap<Integer,List<Integer>>map=new HashMap<>();
        int r=isConnected.length;
        int c=isConnected[0].length;

        for(int i=0;i<r;i++){
            map.putIfAbsent(i,new ArrayList<>());
            for(int j=0;j<c;j++){
                if(i==j)continue;
                map.putIfAbsent(j,new ArrayList<>());
                if(isConnected[i][j]==1){
                    map.get(i).add(j);
                    map.get(j).add(i);
                }
            }
        }
        int count=0;
        HashSet<Integer>visited=new HashSet<>();
        for(int src:map.keySet()){
            if(!visited.contains(src)){
                count++;
                dfs(src,map,visited);
            }
        }
        return count;
    }
    public void dfs(int src,HashMap<Integer,List<Integer>>map,HashSet<Integer>visited){
        if(visited.contains(src))return;
        visited.add(src);
        List<Integer>neighbours=map.get(src);
        for(int val:neighbours){
            if(!visited.contains(val)){
                dfs(val,map,visited);
                visited.add(val);
            }
        }
    }
}

       
